# SwiftFormat config for tinygpt (native-mac Swift).
#
# Goal: enforce the existing house style as a regression gate. The
# codebase has its own multi-space-alignment / column-aligned-comment
# style that doesn't line up with swiftformat's defaults, so we opt-in
# via `--rules` to ONLY the rules the codebase already conforms to.
# Lint mode (`swiftformat --lint`) fails CI on drift; running
# `swiftformat native-mac/Sources native-mac/Tests` (no --lint) auto-
# fixes.
#
# Rules we don't enable — and why:
#   indent / consecutiveSpaces — code uses column-aligned comments and
#       8-space continuation indent in MLX argument lists.
#   spaceAroundOperators — `let a = b*c + d*e` is intentional in math-
#       heavy MLX code; auto-format would space every `*` and `+`.
#   redundantSelf — SwiftUI views use `self.foo` for clarity.
#   hoistPatternLet — `case let .foo(x)` style is preferred at a few
#       SFT / DPO sites and gets used as documentation.
#   wrapPropertyBodies / wrapFunctionBodies — many one-liners like
#       `public var isMoE: Bool { nExperts > 1 }` are clearer compact.
#   andOperator — `&&` vs `,` choice is per-site; some `if let` chains
#       intentionally use `,`, others `&&`. Not worth automating.
#   sortImports — the codebase isn't strictly alphabetical (test files
#       put `@testable` at the bottom; some sources keep MLX adjacent).
#
# Scope: native-mac Swift sources + tests only. The browser TS / WGSL /
# Python paths are linted by their own tools.

--exclude .build,**/.build,**/.swiftpm,build,DerivedData,Pods
--swiftversion 6.0

# Enable ONLY this curated set. Everything else is implicitly disabled.
--rules linebreakAtEndOfFile
--rules duplicateImports
--rules semicolons
--rules void
--rules todos
--rules spaceInsideBrackets
--rules spaceInsideParens
--rules spaceAroundBraces
--rules spaceAroundComments
--rules spaceInsideComments
--rules emptyBraces
--rules initCoderUnavailable
--rules typeSugar
--rules redundantInternal
--rules isEmpty
--rules strongOutlets
--rules strongifiedSelf
--rules headerFileName
--rules redundantBackticks
--rules redundantBreak
--rules redundantExtensionACL
--rules redundantFileprivate
--rules redundantGet
--rules redundantInit
--rules redundantPublic
--rules redundantClosure
